Critical rules:
- Do not rebuild Phase 01–09.
- Do not remove Phase 7.10 collaboration/federation behavior.
- Do not change backend port from 8005.
- Do not introduce localhost:8000 anywhere.
- Do not commit .env, secrets, gpg-loopback.sh, or local agent cache.
- Do not expose secrets in frontend.
- Do not log passwords, JWTs, API keys, refresh tokens, Stripe secrets, Cloudflare tokens, tunnel tokens, or provider tokens.
- Do not store raw credit card data.
- Do not implement custom card processing.
- Payment provider integration must use tokenized provider references only.
- Mock billing must be default in development.
- Real Stripe mode must require explicit provider config.
- Usage quotas must fail safely.
- Enterprise license must not weaken production safety locks.
- Plugin runtime must default to sandbox.
- Plugins must not access secrets by default.
- Plugins must not use external network by default.
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Cloudflare operator automation belongs in cvsz/zeaz-platform, not cvsz/zdash.

